    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cincin.</placeName>
                <date>Sept. 5613</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Revd I Leesor</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I frequently feel an inclination to correspond with your
                use-<lb/>ful magazine on matters connected with religion and the public
                procee-<lb/>ding of congregation affairs, which take place within our sphere</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our object is that such communications be only used when an<lb/>
                opportunity presents itself. I notice this perceiving you have an<lb/> agent in this
                city. I should much wish to know <sic>throug</sic>
                <persName>Mr. N<lb/> Matyer</persName> whither such communications will be
                acceptable.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The <persName>Revd. Dr. Wise</persName> of
                    <placeName>Albany</placeName> has been invited to attend<lb/> at the
                consecration of our new Synagogue which is to take place<lb/> the <date>14th
                    Sept</date>. Int. We are also informed that he will be the guest<lb/> of
                    <persName>Mr. Elias Mayors</persName>, this latter gent. and a party are
                exerting<lb/> their influence to establish a school for the purpose of
                Educa<lb/>ting the children of our persuasion. The Laws of God and the duties<lb/>
                resulting therefrom, in conjunction with the <hi rend="underline">Charterd
                    Talmud</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Yelodim</hi> of the Baai Jeshurun. It is <sic>intend</sic> to
                vest the government of<lb/> the school in the hands of the <persName>Red Dr.
                    Wise</persName>, who is also to be created the<lb/>
                <sic>the</sic> spiritual Instructor of the joint congregation, Bnai Jeshurun<lb/>
                and Bnai Israel, and to preach every <date>Sab.</date> alternately in each of<lb/>
                their Synagogues, the move is a good one, such a union would mater<lb/>ialy lighten
                expenses, but <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> has not the shadow of a chance<lb/> of
                ever being <sic>allowd</sic> to deliver a <hi rend="underline">single</hi> discourse
                in our Synagogue,<lb/> much more to have an <sic>offical</sic> appointment we have
                great reason<lb/> to believe that the Dr. will be the successor of the <persName>Rd
                    I. Rosenfelt</persName> with<lb/> the K. K. B. J. their principal leaders
                declare that <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> has<lb/> done more good already in
                    <placeName>Albany</placeName> than any man in this country.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">yours very Respy</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Saml. Bruel</persName>
            </p>
            <p>K.K.B I. The Annual Election took place this<lb/> Evening, the following persons were
                chosen to serve for one year<lb/>
                <persName>Ferdinand Milias</persName> Parnass. <persName>N. Maltzer</persName>
                <persName>zab Zedokah</persName>, <persName role="author">S. Bruel</persName>
                <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>
                <persName>Isaac Wolf</persName> Treasurer, <persName>Jospht.</persName> Secy.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Sept. 4th</date>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>N. B</p>
            <p>We have never had so full an attendance at an Election, as on this
                <sic>ocasion</sic><lb/> the three candidates: <persName>J Jonas</persName>,
                    <persName>Elias Mayer</persName> &amp; <persName>T Milions</persName> were
                busily engaged<lb/> for some time pass' (through their funds) canvasing. The
                officers <sic>ellected</sic><lb/> are popular persons. The election of this Earning
                decides the fate of <persName>Dr.<lb/> Wise</persName> with our congregation</p>
        </body>
